37// Return true iff the name is valid for Generators or Params.
38// (NOTE: gcc didn't add proper std::regex support until v4.9;
39// we don't yet require this, hence the hand-rolled replacement.)
40
41bool is_alpha(char c) {
42 return (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') || (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z');
43}
44
45// Note that this includes '_'
46bool is_alnum(char c) {
47 return is_alpha(c) || (c == '_') || (c >= '0' && c <= '9');
48}
49
50// Basically, a valid C identifier, except:
51//
52// -- initial _ is forbidden (rather than merely "reserved")
53// -- two underscores in a row is also forbidden
54bool is_valid_name(const std::string &n) {
55 if (n.empty()) {
56 return false;
57 }
58 if (!is_alpha(n[0])) {
59 return false;
60 }
61 for (size_t i = 1; i < n.size(); ++i) {
62 if (!is_alnum(n[i])) {
63 return false;
64 }
65 if (n[i] == '_' && n[i - 1] == '_') {
66 return false;
67 }
68 }
69 return true;
70}

72std::string compute_base_path(const std::string &output_dir,
73 const std::string &function_name,
74 const std::string &file_base_name) {
75 std::vector<std::string> namespaces;
76 std::string simple_name = extract_namespaces(function_name, namespaces);
77 std::string base_path = output_dir + "/" + (file_base_name.empty() ? simple_name : file_base_name);
78 return base_path;
79}

81std::map<Output, std::string> compute_output_files(const Target &target,
82 const std::string &base_path,
83 const std::set<Output> &outputs) {
84 std::map<Output, const OutputInfo> output_info = get_output_info(target);
85
86 std::map<Output, std::string> output_files;
87 for (auto o : outputs) {
88 output_files[o] = base_path + output_info.at(o).extension;
89 }
90 return output_files;
91}

101Func make_param_func(const Parameter &p, const std::string &name) {
102 internal_assert(p.is_buffer());
103 Func f(name + "_im");
104 auto b = p.buffer();
105 if (b.defined()) {
106 // If the Parameter has an explicit BufferPtr set, bind directly to it
107 f(_) = b(_);
108 } else {
109 std::vector<Var> args;
110 std::vector<Expr> args_expr;
111 for (int i = 0; i < p.dimensions(); ++i) {
112 Var v = Var::implicit(i);
113 args.push_back(v);
114 args_expr.push_back(v);
115 }
116 f(args) = Internal::Call::make(p, args_expr);
117 }
118 return f;
119}

123std::vector<Type> parse_halide_type_list(const std::string &types) {
124 const auto &e = get_halide_type_enum_map();
125 std::vector<Type> result;
126 for (const auto &t : split_string(types, ",")) {
127 auto it = e.find(t);
128 user_assert(it != e.end()) << "Type not found: " << t;
129 result.push_back(it->second);
130 }
131 return result;
132}

134void ValueTracker::track_values(const std::string &name, const std::vector<Expr> &values) {
135 std::vector<std::vector<Expr>> &history = values_history[name];
136 if (history.empty()) {
137 for (size_t i = 0; i < values.size(); ++i) {
138 history.push_back({values[i]});
139 }
140 return;
141 }
142
143 internal_assert(history.size() == values.size())
144 << "Expected values of size " << history.size()
145 << " but saw size " << values.size()
146 << " for name " << name << "\n";
147
148 // For each item, see if we have a new unique value
149 for (size_t i = 0; i < values.size(); ++i) {
150 Expr oldval = history[i].back();
151 Expr newval = values[i];
152 if (oldval.defined() && newval.defined()) {
153 if (can_prove(newval == oldval)) {
154 continue;
155 }
156 } else if (!oldval.defined() && !newval.defined()) {
157 // Expr::operator== doesn't work with undefined
158 // values, but they are equal for our purposes here.
159 continue;
160 }
161 history[i].push_back(newval);
162 // If we exceed max_unique_values, fail immediately.
163 // TODO: could be useful to log all the entries that
164 // overflow max_unique_values before failing.
165 // TODO: this could be more helpful about labeling the values
166 // that have multiple setttings.
167 if (history[i].size() > max_unique_values) {
168 std::ostringstream o;
169 o << "Saw too many unique values in ValueTracker[" + std::to_string(i) + "]; "
170 << "expected a maximum of " << max_unique_values << ":\n";
171 for (const auto &e : history[i]) {
172 o << " " << e << "\n";
173 }
174 user_error << o.str();
175 }
176 }
177}

179std::vector<Expr> parameter_constraints(const Parameter &p) {
180 internal_assert(p.defined());
181 std::vector<Expr> values;
182 values.emplace_back(p.host_alignment());
183 if (p.is_buffer()) {
184 for (int i = 0; i < p.dimensions(); ++i) {
185 values.push_back(p.min_constraint(i));
186 values.push_back(p.extent_constraint(i));
187 values.push_back(p.stride_constraint(i));
188 }
189 } else {
190 values.push_back(p.min_value());
191 values.push_back(p.max_value());
192 }
193 return values;
194}

196class StubEmitter {
197public:
198 StubEmitter(std::ostream &dest,
199 const std::string &generator_registered_name,
200 const std::string &generator_stub_name,
201 const std::vector<Internal::GeneratorParamBase *> &generator_params,
202 const std::vector<Internal::GeneratorInputBase *> &inputs,
203 const std::vector<Internal::GeneratorOutputBase *> &outputs)
204 : stream(dest),
205 generator_registered_name(generator_registered_name),
206 generator_stub_name(generator_stub_name),
207 generator_params(select_generator_params(generator_params)),
208 inputs(inputs),
209 outputs(outputs) {
210 namespaces = split_string(generator_stub_name, "::");
211 internal_assert(!namespaces.empty());
212 if (namespaces[0].empty()) {
213 // We have a name like ::foo::bar::baz; omit the first empty ns.
214 namespaces.erase(namespaces.begin());
215 internal_assert(namespaces.size() >= 2);
216 }
217 class_name = namespaces.back();
218 namespaces.pop_back();
219 }

221 void emit();

223private:
224 std::ostream &stream;
225 const std::string generator_registered_name;
226 const std::string generator_stub_name;
227 std::string class_name;
228 std::vector<std::string> namespaces;
229 const std::vector<Internal::GeneratorParamBase *> generator_params;
230 const std::vector<Internal::GeneratorInputBase *> inputs;
231 const std::vector<Internal::GeneratorOutputBase *> outputs;
232 int indent_level{0};

234 std::vector<Internal::GeneratorParamBase *> select_generator_params(const std::vector<Internal::GeneratorParamBase *> &in) {
235 std::vector<Internal::GeneratorParamBase *> out;
236 for (auto *p : in) {
237 // These are always propagated specially.
238 if (p->name() == "target" ||
239 p->name() == "auto_schedule" ||
240 p->name() == "machine_params") {
241 continue;
242 }
243 if (p->is_synthetic_param()) {
244 continue;
245 }
246 out.push_back(p);
247 }
248 return out;
249 }

260void StubEmitter::emit_generator_params_struct() {
261 const auto &v = generator_params;
262 std::string name = "GeneratorParams";
263 stream << get_indent() << "struct " << name << " final {\n";
264 indent_level++;
265 if (!v.empty()) {
266 for (auto *p : v) {
267 stream << get_indent() << p->get_c_type() << " " << p->name() << "{ " << p->get_default_value() << " };\n";
268 }
269 stream << "\n";
270 }
271
272 stream << get_indent() << name << "() {}\n";
273 stream << "\n";
274
275 if (!v.empty()) {
276 stream << get_indent() << name << "(\n";
277 indent_level++;
278 std::string comma = "";
279 for (auto *p : v) {
280 stream << get_indent() << comma << p->get_c_type() << " " << p->name() << "\n";
281 comma = ", ";
282 }
283 indent_level--;
284 stream << get_indent() << ") : \n";
285 indent_level++;
286 comma = "";
287 for (auto *p : v) {
288 stream << get_indent() << comma << p->name() << "(" << p->name() << ")\n";
289 comma = ", ";
290 }
291 indent_level--;
292 stream << get_indent() << "{\n";
293 stream << get_indent() << "}\n";
294 stream << "\n";
295 }
296
297 stream << get_indent() << "inline HALIDE_NO_USER_CODE_INLINE Halide::Internal::GeneratorParamsMap to_generator_params_map() const {\n";
298 indent_level++;
299 stream << get_indent() << "return {\n";
300 indent_level++;
301 std::string comma = "";
302 for (auto *p : v) {
303 stream << get_indent() << comma << "{\"" << p->name() << "\", ";
304 if (p->is_looplevel_param()) {
305 stream << p->name() << "}\n";
306 } else {
307 stream << p->call_to_string(p->name()) << "}\n";
308 }
309 comma = ", ";
310 }
311 indent_level--;
312 stream << get_indent() << "};\n";
313 indent_level--;
314 stream << get_indent() << "}\n";
315
316 indent_level--;
317 stream << get_indent() << "};\n";
318 stream << "\n";
319}

321void StubEmitter::emit_inputs_struct() {
322 struct InInfo {
323 std::string c_type;
324 std::string name;
325 };
326 std::vector<InInfo> in_info;
327 for (auto *input : inputs) {
328 std::string c_type = input->get_c_type();
329 if (input->is_array()) {
330 c_type = "std::vector<" + c_type + ">";
331 }
332 in_info.push_back({c_type, input->name()});
333 }
334
335 const std::string name = "Inputs";
336 stream << get_indent() << "struct " << name << " final {\n";
337 indent_level++;
338 for (const auto &in : in_info) {
339 stream << get_indent() << in.c_type << " " << in.name << ";\n";
340 }
341 stream << "\n";
342
343 stream << get_indent() << name << "() {}\n";
344 stream << "\n";
345 if (!in_info.empty()) {
346 stream << get_indent() << name << "(\n";
347 indent_level++;
348 std::string comma = "";
349 for (const auto &in : in_info) {
350 stream << get_indent() << comma << "const " << in.c_type << "& " << in.name << "\n";
351 comma = ", ";
352 }
353 indent_level--;
354 stream << get_indent() << ") : \n";
355 indent_level++;
356 comma = "";
357 for (const auto &in : in_info) {
358 stream << get_indent() << comma << in.name << "(" << in.name << ")\n";
359 comma = ", ";
360 }
361 indent_level--;
362 stream << get_indent() << "{\n";
363 stream << get_indent() << "}\n";
364
365 indent_level--;
366 }
367 stream << get_indent() << "};\n";
368 stream << "\n";
369}

371void StubEmitter::emit() {
372 if (outputs.empty()) {
373 // The generator can't support a real stub. Instead, generate an (essentially)
374 // empty .stub.h file, so that build systems like Bazel will still get the output file
375 // they expected. Note that we deliberately don't emit an ifndef header guard,
376 // since we can't reliably assume that the generator_name will be globally unique;
377 // on the other hand, since this file is just a couple of comments, it's
378 // really not an issue if it's included multiple times.
379 stream << "/* MACHINE-GENERATED - DO NOT EDIT */\n";
380 stream << "/* The Generator named " << generator_registered_name << " uses ImageParam or Param, thus cannot have a Stub generated. */\n";
381 return;
382 }
383
384 struct OutputInfo {
385 std::string name;
386 std::string ctype;
387 std::string getter;
388 };
389 bool all_outputs_are_func = true;
390 std::vector<OutputInfo> out_info;
391 for (auto *output : outputs) {
392 std::string c_type = output->get_c_type();
393 const bool is_func = (c_type == "Func");
394 std::string getter = is_func ? "get_outputs" : "get_output_buffers<" + c_type + ">";
395 std::string getter_suffix = output->is_array() ? "" : ".at(0)";
396 out_info.push_back({output->name(),
397 output->is_array() ? "std::vector<" + c_type + ">" : c_type,
398 getter + "(\"" + output->name() + "\")" + getter_suffix});
399 if (c_type != "Func") {
400 all_outputs_are_func = false;
401 }
402 }
403
404 std::ostringstream guard;
405 guard << "HALIDE_STUB";
406 for (const auto &ns : namespaces) {
407 guard << "_" << ns;
408 }
409 guard << "_" << class_name;
410
411 stream << get_indent() << "#ifndef " << guard.str() << "\n";
412 stream << get_indent() << "#define " << guard.str() << "\n";
413 stream << "\n";
414
415 stream << get_indent() << "/* MACHINE-GENERATED - DO NOT EDIT */\n";
416 stream << "\n";
417
418 stream << get_indent() << "#include <cassert>\n";
419 stream << get_indent() << "#include <map>\n";
420 stream << get_indent() << "#include <memory>\n";
421 stream << get_indent() << "#include <string>\n";
422 stream << get_indent() << "#include <utility>\n";
423 stream << get_indent() << "#include <vector>\n";
424 stream << "\n";
425 stream << get_indent() << "#include \"Halide.h\"\n";
426 stream << "\n";
427
428 stream << "namespace halide_register_generator {\n";
429 stream << "namespace " << generator_registered_name << "_ns {\n";
430 stream << "extern std::unique_ptr<Halide::Internal::GeneratorBase> factory(const Halide::GeneratorContext& context);\n";
431 stream << "} // namespace halide_register_generator\n";
432 stream << "} // namespace " << generator_registered_name << "\n";
433 stream << "\n";
434
435 for (const auto &ns : namespaces) {
436 stream << get_indent() << "namespace " << ns << " {\n";
437 }
438 stream << "\n";
439
440 for (auto *p : generator_params) {
441 std::string decl = p->get_type_decls();
442 if (decl.empty()) {
443 continue;
444 }
445 stream << decl << "\n";
446 }
447
448 stream << get_indent() << "class " << class_name << " final : public Halide::NamesInterface {\n";
449 stream << get_indent() << "public:\n";
450 indent_level++;
451
452 emit_inputs_struct();
453 emit_generator_params_struct();
454
455 stream << get_indent() << "struct Outputs final {\n";
456 indent_level++;
457 stream << get_indent() << "// Outputs\n";
458 for (const auto &out : out_info) {
459 stream << get_indent() << out.ctype << " " << out.name << ";\n";
460 }
461
462 stream << "\n";
463 stream << get_indent() << "// The Target used\n";
464 stream << get_indent() << "Target target;\n";
465
466 if (out_info.size() == 1) {
467 stream << "\n";
468 if (all_outputs_are_func) {
469 std::string name = out_info.at(0).name;
470 auto *output = outputs[0];
471 if (output->is_array()) {
472 stream << get_indent() << "operator std::vector<Halide::Func>() const {\n";
473 indent_level++;
474 stream << get_indent() << "return " << name << ";\n";
475 indent_level--;
476 stream << get_indent() << "}\n";
477
478 stream << get_indent() << "Halide::Func operator[](size_t i) const {\n";
479 indent_level++;
480 stream << get_indent() << "return " << name << "[i];\n";
481 indent_level--;
482 stream << get_indent() << "}\n";
483
484 stream << get_indent() << "Halide::Func at(size_t i) const {\n";
485 indent_level++;
486 stream << get_indent() << "return " << name << ".at(i);\n";
487 indent_level--;
488 stream << get_indent() << "}\n";
489
490 stream << get_indent() << "// operator operator()() overloads omitted because the sole Output is array-of-Func.\n";
491 } else {
492 // If there is exactly one output, add overloads
493 // for operator Func and operator().
494 stream << get_indent() << "operator Halide::Func() const {\n";
495 indent_level++;
496 stream << get_indent() << "return " << name << ";\n";
497 indent_level--;
498 stream << get_indent() << "}\n";
499
500 stream << "\n";
501 stream << get_indent() << "template <typename... Args>\n";
502 stream << get_indent() << "Halide::FuncRef operator()(Args&&... args) const {\n";
503 indent_level++;
504 stream << get_indent() << "return " << name << "(std::forward<Args>(args)...);\n";
505 indent_level--;
506 stream << get_indent() << "}\n";
507
508 stream << "\n";
509 stream << get_indent() << "template <typename ExprOrVar>\n";
510 stream << get_indent() << "Halide::FuncRef operator()(std::vector<ExprOrVar> args) const {\n";
511 indent_level++;
512 stream << get_indent() << "return " << name << "()(args);\n";
513 indent_level--;
514 stream << get_indent() << "}\n";
515 }
516 } else {
517 stream << get_indent() << "// operator Func() and operator()() overloads omitted because the sole Output is not Func.\n";
518 }
519 }
520
521 stream << "\n";
522 if (all_outputs_are_func) {
523 stream << get_indent() << "Halide::Pipeline get_pipeline() const {\n";
524 indent_level++;
525 stream << get_indent() << "return Halide::Pipeline(std::vector<Halide::Func>{\n";
526 indent_level++;
527 int commas = (int)out_info.size() - 1;
528 for (const auto &out : out_info) {
529 stream << get_indent() << out.name << (commas-- ? "," : "") << "\n";
530 }
531 indent_level--;
532 stream << get_indent() << "});\n";
533 indent_level--;
534 stream << get_indent() << "}\n";
535
536 stream << "\n";
537 stream << get_indent() << "Halide::Realization realize(std::vector<int32_t> sizes) {\n";
538 indent_level++;
539 stream << get_indent() << "return get_pipeline().realize(sizes, target);\n";
540 indent_level--;
541 stream << get_indent() << "}\n";
542
543 stream << "\n";
544 stream << get_indent() << "template <typename... Args, typename std::enable_if<Halide::Internal::NoRealizations<Args...>::value>::type * = nullptr>\n";
545 stream << get_indent() << "Halide::Realization realize(Args&&... args) {\n";
546 indent_level++;
547 stream << get_indent() << "return get_pipeline().realize(std::forward<Args>(args)..., target);\n";
548 indent_level--;
549 stream << get_indent() << "}\n";
550
551 stream << "\n";
552 stream << get_indent() << "void realize(Halide::Realization r) {\n";
553 indent_level++;
554 stream << get_indent() << "get_pipeline().realize(r, target);\n";
555 indent_level--;
556 stream << get_indent() << "}\n";
557 } else {
558 stream << get_indent() << "// get_pipeline() and realize() overloads omitted because some Outputs are not Func.\n";
559 }
560
561 indent_level--;
562 stream << get_indent() << "};\n";
563 stream << "\n";
564
565 stream << get_indent() << "HALIDE_NO_USER_CODE_INLINE static Outputs generate(\n";
566 indent_level++;
567 stream << get_indent() << "const GeneratorContext& context,\n";
568 stream << get_indent() << "const Inputs& inputs,\n";
569 stream << get_indent() << "const GeneratorParams& generator_params = GeneratorParams()\n";
570 indent_level--;
571 stream << get_indent() << ")\n";
572 stream << get_indent() << "{\n";
573 indent_level++;
574 stream << get_indent() << "using Stub = Halide::Internal::GeneratorStub;\n";
575 stream << get_indent() << "Stub stub(\n";
576 indent_level++;
577 stream << get_indent() << "context,\n";
578 stream << get_indent() << "halide_register_generator::" << generator_registered_name << "_ns::factory,\n";
579 stream << get_indent() << "generator_params.to_generator_params_map(),\n";
580 stream << get_indent() << "{\n";
581 indent_level++;
582 for (size_t i = 0; i < inputs.size(); ++i) {
583 stream << get_indent() << "Stub::to_stub_input_vector(inputs." << inputs[i]->name() << ")";
584 stream << ",\n";
585 }
586 indent_level--;
587 stream << get_indent() << "}\n";
588 indent_level--;
589 stream << get_indent() << ");\n";
590
591 stream << get_indent() << "return {\n";
592 indent_level++;
593 for (const auto &out : out_info) {
594 stream << get_indent() << "stub." << out.getter << ",\n";
595 }
596 stream << get_indent() << "stub.generator->get_target()\n";
597 indent_level--;
598 stream << get_indent() << "};\n";
599 indent_level--;
600 stream << get_indent() << "}\n";
601 stream << "\n";
602
603 stream << get_indent() << "// overload to allow GeneratorContext-pointer\n";
604 stream << get_indent() << "inline static Outputs generate(\n";
605 indent_level++;
606 stream << get_indent() << "const GeneratorContext* context,\n";
607 stream << get_indent() << "const Inputs& inputs,\n";
608 stream << get_indent() << "const GeneratorParams& generator_params = GeneratorParams()\n";
609 indent_level--;
610 stream << get_indent() << ")\n";
611 stream << get_indent() << "{\n";
612 indent_level++;
613 stream << get_indent() << "return generate(*context, inputs, generator_params);\n";
614 indent_level--;
615 stream << get_indent() << "}\n";
616 stream << "\n";
617
618 stream << get_indent() << "// overload to allow Target instead of GeneratorContext.\n";
619 stream << get_indent() << "inline static Outputs generate(\n";
620 indent_level++;
621 stream << get_indent() << "const Target& target,\n";
622 stream << get_indent() << "const Inputs& inputs,\n";
623 stream << get_indent() << "const GeneratorParams& generator_params = GeneratorParams()\n";
624 indent_level--;
625 stream << get_indent() << ")\n";
626 stream << get_indent() << "{\n";
627 indent_level++;
628 stream << get_indent() << "return generate(Halide::GeneratorContext(target), inputs, generator_params);\n";
629 indent_level--;
630 stream << get_indent() << "}\n";
631 stream << "\n";
632
633 stream << get_indent() << class_name << "() = delete;\n";
634
635 indent_level--;
636 stream << get_indent() << "};\n";
637 stream << "\n";
638
639 for (int i = (int)namespaces.size() - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
640 stream << get_indent() << "} // namespace " << namespaces[i] << "\n";
641 }
642 stream << "\n";
643
644 stream << get_indent() << "#endif // " << guard.str() << "\n";
645}

660// Return a vector of all Outputs of this Generator; non-array outputs are returned
661// as a vector-of-size-1. This method is primarily useful for code that needs
662// to iterate through the outputs of unknown, arbitrary Generators (e.g.,
663// the Python bindings).
664std::vector<std::vector<Func>> GeneratorStub::generate(const GeneratorParamsMap &generator_params,
665 const std::vector<std::vector<Internal::StubInput>> &inputs) {
666 generator->set_generator_param_values(generator_params);
667 generator->ensure_configure_has_been_called();
668 generator->set_inputs_vector(inputs);
669 Pipeline p = generator->build_pipeline();
670
671 std::vector<std::vector<Func>> v;
672 GeneratorParamInfo &pi = generator->param_info();
673 if (!pi.outputs().empty()) {
674 for (auto *output : pi.outputs()) {
675 v.push_back(get_outputs(output->name()));
676 }
677 } else {
678 // Generators with build() method can't have Output<>, hence can't have array outputs
679 for (const auto &output : p.outputs()) {
680 v.push_back(std::vector<Func>{output});
681 }
682 }
683 return v;
684}
685
686GeneratorStub::Names GeneratorStub::get_names() const {
687 generator->ensure_configure_has_been_called();
688 auto &pi = generator->param_info();
689 Names names;
690 for (auto *o : pi.generator_params()) {
691 names.generator_params.push_back(o->name());
692 }
693 for (auto *o : pi.inputs()) {
694 names.inputs.push_back(o->name());
695 }
696 for (auto *o : pi.outputs()) {
697 names.outputs.push_back(o->name());
698 }
699 return names;
700}

702const std::map<std::string, Type> &get_halide_type_enum_map() {
703 static const std::map<std::string, Type> halide_type_enum_map{
704 {"bool", Bool()},
705 {"int8", Int(8)},
706 {"int16", Int(16)},
707 {"int32", Int(32)},
708 {"uint8", UInt(8)},
709 {"uint16", UInt(16)},
710 {"uint32", UInt(32)},
711 {"float16", Float(16)},
712 {"float32", Float(32)},
713 {"float64", Float(64)}};
714 return halide_type_enum_map;
715}
716
717std::string halide_type_to_c_source(const Type &t) {
718 static const std::map<halide_type_code_t, std::string> m = {
719 {halide_type_int, "Int"},
720 {halide_type_uint, "UInt"},
721 {halide_type_float, "Float"},
722 {halide_type_handle, "Handle"},
723 };
724 std::ostringstream oss;
725 oss << "Halide::" << m.at(t.code()) << "(" << t.bits() << +")";
726 return oss.str();
727}
728
729std::string halide_type_to_c_type(const Type &t) {
730 auto encode = [](const Type &t) -> int { return t.code() << 16 | t.bits(); };
731 static const std::map<int, std::string> m = {
732 {encode(Int(8)), "int8_t"},
733 {encode(Int(16)), "int16_t"},
734 {encode(Int(32)), "int32_t"},
735 {encode(Int(64)), "int64_t"},
736 {encode(UInt(1)), "bool"},
737 {encode(UInt(8)), "uint8_t"},
738 {encode(UInt(16)), "uint16_t"},
739 {encode(UInt(32)), "uint32_t"},
740 {encode(UInt(64)), "uint64_t"},
741 {encode(BFloat(16)), "uint16_t"}, // TODO: see Issues #3709, #3967
742 {encode(Float(16)), "uint16_t"}, // TODO: see Issues #3709, #3967
743 {encode(Float(32)), "float"},
744 {encode(Float(64)), "double"},
745 {encode(Handle(64)), "void*"}};
746 internal_assert(m.count(encode(t))) << t << " " << encode(t);
747 return m.at(encode(t));
748}
749
750int generate_filter_main_inner(int argc, char **argv, std::ostream &error_output) {
751 const char kUsage[] =
752 "gengen\n"
753 " [-g GENERATOR_NAME] [-f FUNCTION_NAME] [-o OUTPUT_DIR] [-r RUNTIME_NAME] [-d 1|0]\n"
754 " [-e EMIT_OPTIONS] [-n FILE_BASE_NAME] [-p PLUGIN_NAME] [-s AUTOSCHEDULER_NAME]\n"
755 " target=target-string[,target-string...] [generator_arg=value [...]]\n"
756 "\n"
757 " -d Build a module that is suitable for using for gradient descent calculationn\n"
758 " in TensorFlow or PyTorch. See Generator::build_gradient_module() documentation.\n"
759 "\n"
760 " -e A comma separated list of files to emit. Accepted values are:\n"
761 " [assembly, bitcode, c_header, c_source, cpp_stub, featurization,\n"
762 " llvm_assembly, object, python_extension, pytorch_wrapper, registration,\n"
763 " schedule, static_library, stmt, stmt_html, compiler_log].\n"
764 " If omitted, default value is [c_header, static_library, registration].\n"
765 "\n"
766 " -p A comma-separated list of shared libraries that will be loaded before the\n"
767 " generator is run. Useful for custom auto-schedulers. The generator must\n"
768 " either be linked against a shared libHalide or compiled with -rdynamic\n"
769 " so that references in the shared library to libHalide can resolve.\n"
770 " (Note that this does not change the default autoscheduler; use the -s flag\n"
771 " to set that value.)"
772 "\n"
773 " -r The name of a standalone runtime to generate. Only honors EMIT_OPTIONS 'o'\n"
774 " and 'static_library'. When multiple targets are specified, it picks a\n"
775 " runtime that is compatible with all of the targets, or fails if it cannot\n"
776 " find one. Flags across all of the targets that do not affect runtime code\n"
777 " generation, such as `no_asserts` and `no_runtime`, are ignored.\n"
778 "\n"
779 " -s The name of an autoscheduler to set as the default.\n";
780
781 std::map<std::string, std::string> flags_info = {
782 {"-d", "0"},
783 {"-e", ""},
784 {"-f", ""},
785 {"-g", ""},
786 {"-n", ""},
787 {"-o", ""},
788 {"-p", ""},
789 {"-r", ""},
790 {"-s", ""},
791 };
792 GeneratorParamsMap generator_args;
793
794 for (int i = 1; i < argc; ++i) {
795 if (argv[i][0] != '-') {
796 std::vector<std::string> v = split_string(argv[i], "=");
797 if (v.size() != 2 || v[0].empty() || v[1].empty()) {
798 error_output << kUsage;
799 return 1;
800 }
801 generator_args[v[0]] = v[1];
802 continue;
803 }
804 auto it = flags_info.find(argv[i]);
805 if (it != flags_info.end()) {
806 if (i + 1 >= argc) {
807 error_output << kUsage;
808 return 1;
809 }
810 it->second = argv[i + 1];
811 ++i;
812 continue;
813 }
814 error_output << "Unknown flag: " << argv[i] << "\n";
815 error_output << kUsage;
816 return 1;
817 }
818
819 // It's possible that in the future loaded plugins might change
820 // how arguments are parsed, so we handle those first.
821 for (const auto &lib : split_string(flags_info["-p"], ",")) {
822 if (!lib.empty()) {
823 load_plugin(lib);
824 }
825 }
826
827 if (flags_info["-d"] != "1" && flags_info["-d"] != "0") {
828 error_output << "-d must be 0 or 1\n";
829 error_output << kUsage;
830 return 1;
831 }
832 const int build_gradient_module = flags_info["-d"] == "1";
833
834 std::string autoscheduler_name = flags_info["-s"];
835 if (!autoscheduler_name.empty()) {
836 Pipeline::set_default_autoscheduler_name(autoscheduler_name);
837 }
838
839 std::string runtime_name = flags_info["-r"];
840
841 std::vector<std::string> generator_names = GeneratorRegistry::enumerate();
842 if (generator_names.empty() && runtime_name.empty()) {
843 error_output << "No generators have been registered and not compiling a standalone runtime\n";
844 error_output << kUsage;
845 return 1;
846 }
847
848 std::string generator_name = flags_info["-g"];
849 if (generator_name.empty() && runtime_name.empty()) {
850 // Require either -g or -r to be specified:
851 // no longer infer the name when only one Generator is registered
852 error_output << "Either -g <name> or -r must be specified; available Generators are:\n";
853 if (!generator_names.empty()) {
854 for (const auto &name : generator_names) {
855 error_output << " " << name << "\n";
856 }
857 } else {
858 error_output << " <none>\n";
859 }
860 return 1;
861 }
862
863 std::string function_name = flags_info["-f"];
864 if (function_name.empty()) {
865 // If -f isn't specified, assume function name = generator name.
866 function_name = generator_name;
867 }
868 std::string output_dir = flags_info["-o"];
869 if (output_dir.empty()) {
870 error_output << "-o must always be specified.\n";
871 error_output << kUsage;
872 return 1;
873 }
874
875 std::string emit_flags_string = flags_info["-e"];
876
877 // If HL_EXTRA_OUTPUTS is defined, assume it's extra outputs we want to generate
878 // (usually for temporary debugging purposes) and just tack it on to the -e contents.
879 std::string extra_outputs = get_env_variable("HL_EXTRA_OUTPUTS");
880 if (!extra_outputs.empty()) {
881 if (!emit_flags_string.empty()) {
882 emit_flags_string += ",";
883 }
884 emit_flags_string += extra_outputs;
885 }
886
887 // It's ok to omit "target=" if we are generating *only* a cpp_stub
888 const std::vector<std::string> emit_flags = split_string(emit_flags_string, ",");
889 const bool stub_only = (emit_flags.size() == 1 && emit_flags[0] == "cpp_stub");
890 if (!stub_only) {
891 if (generator_args.find("target") == generator_args.end()) {
892 error_output << "Target missing\n";
893 error_output << kUsage;
894 return 1;
895 }
896 }
897
898 // it's OK for file_base_name to be empty: filename will be based on function name
899 std::string file_base_name = flags_info["-n"];
900
901 auto target_strings = split_string(generator_args["target"].string_value, ",");
902 std::vector<Target> targets;
903 for (const auto &s : target_strings) {
904 targets.emplace_back(s);
905 }
906
907 // extensions won't vary across multitarget output
908 std::map<Output, const OutputInfo> output_info = get_output_info(targets[0]);
909
910 std::set<Output> outputs;
911 if (emit_flags.empty() || (emit_flags.size() == 1 && emit_flags[0].empty())) {
912 // If omitted or empty, assume .a and .h and registration.cpp
913 outputs.insert(Output::c_header);
914 outputs.insert(Output::registration);
915 outputs.insert(Output::static_library);
916 } else {
917 // Build a reverse lookup table. Allow some legacy aliases on the command line,
918 // to allow legacy build systems to work more easily.
919 std::map<std::string, Output> output_name_to_enum = {
920 {"cpp", Output::c_source},
921 {"h", Output::c_header},
922 {"html", Output::stmt_html},
923 {"o", Output::object},
924 {"py.c", Output::python_extension},
925 };
926 for (const auto &it : output_info) {
927 output_name_to_enum[it.second.name] = it.first;
928 }
929
930 for (const std::string &opt : emit_flags) {
931 auto it = output_name_to_enum.find(opt);
932 if (it == output_name_to_enum.end()) {
933 error_output << "Unrecognized emit option: " << opt << " is not one of [";
934 auto end = output_info.cend();
935 auto last = std::prev(end);
936 for (auto iter = output_info.cbegin(); iter != end; ++iter) {
937 error_output << iter->second.name;
938 if (iter != last) {
939 error_output << " ";
940 }
941 }
942 error_output << "], ignoring.\n";
943 error_output << kUsage;
944 return 1;
945 }
946 outputs.insert(it->second);
947 }
948 }
949
950 // Allow quick-n-dirty use of compiler logging via HL_DEBUG_COMPILER_LOGGER env var
951 const bool do_compiler_logging = outputs.count(Output::compiler_log) ||
952 (get_env_variable("HL_DEBUG_COMPILER_LOGGER") == "1");
953
954 const bool obfuscate_compiler_logging = get_env_variable("HL_OBFUSCATE_COMPILER_LOGGER") == "1";
955
956 const CompilerLoggerFactory no_compiler_logger_factory =
957 [](const std::string &, const Target &) -> std::unique_ptr<CompilerLogger> {
958 return nullptr;
959 };
960
961 const CompilerLoggerFactory json_compiler_logger_factory =
962 [&](const std::string &function_name, const Target &target) -> std::unique_ptr<CompilerLogger> {
963 // rebuild generator_args from the map so that they are always canonical
964 std::string generator_args_string;
965 std::string sep;
966 for (const auto &it : generator_args) {
967 if (it.first == "target") {
968 continue;
969 }
970 std::string quote = it.second.string_value.find(' ') != std::string::npos ? "\\\"" : "";
971 generator_args_string += sep + it.first + "=" + quote + it.second.string_value + quote;
972 sep = " ";
973 }
974 std::unique_ptr<JSONCompilerLogger> t(new JSONCompilerLogger(
975 obfuscate_compiler_logging ? "" : generator_name,
976 obfuscate_compiler_logging ? "" : function_name,
977 obfuscate_compiler_logging ? "" : autoscheduler_name,
978 obfuscate_compiler_logging ? Target() : target,
979 obfuscate_compiler_logging ? "" : generator_args_string,
980 obfuscate_compiler_logging));
981 return t;
982 };
983
984 const CompilerLoggerFactory compiler_logger_factory = do_compiler_logging ?
985 json_compiler_logger_factory :
986 no_compiler_logger_factory;
987
988 if (!runtime_name.empty()) {
989 std::string base_path = compute_base_path(output_dir, runtime_name, "");
990
991 Target gcd_target = targets[0];
992 for (size_t i = 1; i < targets.size(); i++) {
993 if (!gcd_target.get_runtime_compatible_target(targets[i], gcd_target)) {
994 error_output << "Failed to find compatible runtime target for "
995 << gcd_target.to_string()
996 << " and "
997 << targets[i].to_string() << "\n";
998 return -1;
999 }
1000 }
1001
1002 if (targets.size() > 1) {
1003 debug(1) << "Building runtime for computed target: " << gcd_target.to_string() << "\n";
1004 }
1005
1006 auto output_files = compute_output_files(gcd_target, base_path, outputs);
1007 // Runtime doesn't get to participate in the CompilerLogger party
1008 compile_standalone_runtime(output_files, gcd_target);
1009 }
1010
1011 if (!generator_name.empty()) {
1012 std::string base_path = compute_base_path(output_dir, function_name, file_base_name);
1013 debug(1) << "Generator " << generator_name << " has base_path " << base_path << "\n";
1014 if (outputs.count(Output::cpp_stub)) {
1015 // When generating cpp_stub, we ignore all generator args passed in, and supply a fake Target.
1016 // (CompilerLogger is never enabled for cpp_stub, for now anyway.)
1017 auto gen = GeneratorRegistry::create(generator_name, GeneratorContext(Target()));
1018 auto stub_file_path = base_path + output_info[Output::cpp_stub].extension;
1019 gen->emit_cpp_stub(stub_file_path);
1020 }
1021
1022 // Don't bother with this if we're just emitting a cpp_stub.
1023 if (!stub_only) {
1024 auto output_files = compute_output_files(targets[0], base_path, outputs);
1025 auto module_factory = [&generator_name, &generator_args, build_gradient_module](const std::string &name, const Target &target) -> Module {
1026 auto sub_generator_args = generator_args;
1027 sub_generator_args.erase("target");
1028 // Must re-create each time since each instance will have a different Target.
1029 auto gen = GeneratorRegistry::create(generator_name, GeneratorContext(target));
1030 gen->set_generator_param_values(sub_generator_args);
1031 return build_gradient_module ? gen->build_gradient_module(name) : gen->build_module(name);
1032 };
1033 compile_multitarget(function_name, output_files, targets, target_strings, module_factory, compiler_logger_factory);
1034 }
1035 }
1036
1037 return 0;
1038}

1043 return generate_filter_main_inner(argc, argv, cerr);

1046 return -1;
1047 }
1048}

1051 return generate_filter_main_inner(argc, argv, cerr);

1065void GeneratorParamBase::check_value_readable() const {
1066 // These are always readable.
1067 if (name() == "target" ||
1068 name() == "auto_schedule" ||
1069 name() == "machine_params") {
1070 return;
1071 }
1072 user_assert(generator && generator->phase >= GeneratorBase::ConfigureCalled)
1073 << "The GeneratorParam \"" << name() << "\" cannot be read before build() or configure()/generate() is called.\n";
1074}
1075
1076void GeneratorParamBase::check_value_writable() const {
1077 // Allow writing when no Generator is set, to avoid having to special-case ctor initing code
1078 if (!generator) {
1079 return;
1080 }
1081 user_assert(generator->phase < GeneratorBase::GenerateCalled) << "The GeneratorParam \"" << name() << "\" cannot be written after build() or generate() is called.\n";
1082}

1084void GeneratorParamBase::fail_wrong_type(const char *type) {
1085 user_error << "The GeneratorParam \"" << name() << "\" cannot be set with a value of type " << type << ".\n";
1086}

1088/* static */
1089GeneratorRegistry &GeneratorRegistry::get_registry() {
1090 static GeneratorRegistry *registry = new GeneratorRegistry;
1091 return *registry;

1094/* static */
1095void GeneratorRegistry::register_factory(const std::string &name,
1096 GeneratorFactory generator_factory) {
1097 user_assert(is_valid_name(name)) << "Invalid Generator name: " << name;
1098 GeneratorRegistry &registry = get_registry();
1099 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(registry.mutex);
1100 internal_assert(registry.factories.find(name) == registry.factories.end())
1101 << "Duplicate Generator name: " << name;
1102 registry.factories[name] = std::move(generator_factory);
1103}
1104
1105/* static */
1106void GeneratorRegistry::unregister_factory(const std::string &name) {
1107 GeneratorRegistry &registry = get_registry();
1108 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(registry.mutex);
1109 internal_assert(registry.factories.find(name) != registry.factories.end())
1110 << "Generator not found: " << name;
1111 registry.factories.erase(name);
1112}
1113
1114/* static */
1115std::unique_ptr<GeneratorBase> GeneratorRegistry::create(const std::string &name,
1116 const GeneratorContext &context) {
1117 GeneratorRegistry &registry = get_registry();
1118 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(registry.mutex);
1119 auto it = registry.factories.find(name);
1120 if (it == registry.factories.end()) {
1121 std::ostringstream o;
1122 o << "Generator not found: " << name << "\n";
1123 o << "Did you mean:\n";
1124 for (const auto &n : registry.factories) {
1125 o << " " << n.first << "\n";
1126 }
1127 user_error << o.str();
1128 }
1129 std::unique_ptr<GeneratorBase> g = it->second(context);
1130 internal_assert(g != nullptr);
1131 return g;
1132}

1134/* static */
1135std::vector<std::string> GeneratorRegistry::enumerate() {
1136 GeneratorRegistry &registry = get_registry();
1137 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(registry.mutex);
1138 std::vector<std::string> result;
1139 result.reserve(registry.factories.size());
1140 for (const auto &i : registry.factories) {
1141 result.push_back(i.first);
1142 }
1143 return result;
1144}

1154
1155GeneratorParamInfo::GeneratorParamInfo(GeneratorBase *generator, const size_t size) {
1156 std::vector<void *> vf = ObjectInstanceRegistry::instances_in_range(
1157 generator, size, ObjectInstanceRegistry::FilterParam);
1158 user_assert(vf.empty()) << "ImageParam and Param<> are no longer allowed in Generators; use Input<> instead.";
1159
1160 const auto add_synthetic_params = [this, generator](GIOBase *gio) {
1161 const std::string &n = gio->name();
1162 const std::string &gn = generator->generator_registered_name;
1163
1164 owned_synthetic_params.push_back(GeneratorParam_Synthetic<Type>::make(generator, gn, n + ".type", *gio, SyntheticParamType::Type, gio->types_defined()));
1165 filter_generator_params.push_back(owned_synthetic_params.back().get());
1166
1167 if (gio->kind() != IOKind::Scalar) {
1168 owned_synthetic_params.push_back(GeneratorParam_Synthetic<int>::make(generator, gn, n + ".dim", *gio, SyntheticParamType::Dim, gio->dims_defined()));
1169 filter_generator_params.push_back(owned_synthetic_params.back().get());
1170 }
1171 if (gio->is_array()) {
1172 owned_synthetic_params.push_back(GeneratorParam_Synthetic<size_t>::make(generator, gn, n + ".size", *gio, SyntheticParamType::ArraySize, gio->array_size_defined()));
1173 filter_generator_params.push_back(owned_synthetic_params.back().get());
1174 }
1175 };
1176
1177 std::vector<void *> vi = ObjectInstanceRegistry::instances_in_range(
1178 generator, size, ObjectInstanceRegistry::GeneratorInput);
1179 for (auto *v : vi) {
1180 auto *input = static_cast<Internal::GeneratorInputBase *>(v);
1181 internal_assert(input != nullptr);
1182 user_assert(is_valid_name(input->name())) << "Invalid Input name: (" << input->name() << ")\n";
1183 user_assert(!names.count(input->name())) << "Duplicate Input name: " << input->name();
1184 names.insert(input->name());
1185 internal_assert(input->generator == nullptr || input->generator == generator);
1186 input->generator = generator;
1187 filter_inputs.push_back(input);
1188 add_synthetic_params(input);
1189 }
1190
1191 std::vector<void *> vo = ObjectInstanceRegistry::instances_in_range(
1192 generator, size, ObjectInstanceRegistry::GeneratorOutput);
1193 for (auto *v : vo) {
1194 auto *output = static_cast<Internal::GeneratorOutputBase *>(v);
1195 internal_assert(output != nullptr);
1196 user_assert(is_valid_name(output->name())) << "Invalid Output name: (" << output->name() << ")\n";
1197 user_assert(!names.count(output->name())) << "Duplicate Output name: " << output->name();
1198 names.insert(output->name());
1199 internal_assert(output->generator == nullptr || output->generator == generator);
1200 output->generator = generator;
1201 filter_outputs.push_back(output);
1202 add_synthetic_params(output);
1203 }
1204
1205 std::vector<void *> vg = ObjectInstanceRegistry::instances_in_range(
1206 generator, size, ObjectInstanceRegistry::GeneratorParam);
1207 for (auto *v : vg) {
1208 auto *param = static_cast<GeneratorParamBase *>(v);
1209 internal_assert(param != nullptr);
1210 user_assert(is_valid_name(param->name())) << "Invalid GeneratorParam name: " << param->name();
1211 user_assert(!names.count(param->name())) << "Duplicate GeneratorParam name: " << param->name();
1212 names.insert(param->name());
1213 internal_assert(param->generator == nullptr || param->generator == generator);
1214 param->generator = generator;
1215 filter_generator_params.push_back(param);
1216 }
1217
1218 for (auto &g : owned_synthetic_params) {
1219 g->generator = generator;
1220 }
1221}

1224 internal_assert(param_info_ptr != nullptr);

1227
1228std::vector<Func> GeneratorBase::get_outputs(const std::string &n) {
1229 check_min_phase(GenerateCalled);
1230 auto *output = find_output_by_name(n);
1231 // Call for the side-effect of asserting if the value isn't defined.
1232 (void)output->array_size();
1233 for (const auto &f : output->funcs()) {
1234 user_assert(f.defined()) << "Output " << n << " was not fully defined.\n";
1235 }
1236 return output->funcs();
1237}
1238
1239// Find output by name. If not found, assert-fail. Never returns null.
1240GeneratorOutputBase *GeneratorBase::find_output_by_name(const std::string &name) {
1241 // There usually are very few outputs, so a linear search is fine
1242 GeneratorParamInfo &pi = param_info();
1243 for (GeneratorOutputBase *output : pi.outputs()) {
1244 if (output->name() == name) {
1245 return output;
1246 }
1247 }
1248 internal_error << "Output " << name << " not found.";
1249 return nullptr; // not reached
1250}

1252void GeneratorBase::set_generator_param_values(const GeneratorParamsMap &params) {
1253 GeneratorParamInfo &pi = param_info();
1254
1255 std::unordered_map<std::string, Internal::GeneratorParamBase *> generator_params_by_name;
1256 for (auto *g : pi.generator_params()) {
1257 generator_params_by_name[g->name()] = g;
1258 }
1259
1260 for (const auto &key_value : params) {
1261 auto gp = generator_params_by_name.find(key_value.first);
1262 user_assert(gp != generator_params_by_name.end())
1263 << "Generator " << generator_registered_name << " has no GeneratorParam named: " << key_value.first << "\n";
1264 if (gp->second->is_looplevel_param()) {
1265 if (!key_value.second.string_value.empty()) {
1266 gp->second->set_from_string(key_value.second.string_value);
1267 } else {
1268 gp->second->set(key_value.second.loop_level);
1269 }
1270 } else {
1271 gp->second->set_from_string(key_value.second.string_value);
1272 }
1273 }
1274}

1291void GeneratorBase::set_inputs_vector(const std::vector<std::vector<StubInput>> &inputs) {
1292 advance_phase(InputsSet);
1293 internal_assert(!inputs_set) << "set_inputs_vector() must be called at most once per Generator instance.\n";
1294 GeneratorParamInfo &pi = param_info();
1295 user_assert(inputs.size() == pi.inputs().size())
1296 << "Expected exactly " << pi.inputs().size()
1297 << " inputs but got " << inputs.size() << "\n";

1299 pi.inputs()[i]->set_inputs(inputs[i]);
1300 }
1301 inputs_set = true;
1302}
1303
1304void GeneratorBase::track_parameter_values(bool include_outputs) {
1305 GeneratorParamInfo &pi = param_info();
1306 for (auto *input : pi.inputs()) {
1307 if (input->kind() == IOKind::Buffer) {
1308 internal_assert(!input->parameters_.empty());
1309 for (auto &p : input->parameters_) {
1310 // This must use p.name(), *not* input->name()
1311 get_value_tracker()->track_values(p.name(), parameter_constraints(p));
1312 }
1313 }
1314 }
1315 if (include_outputs) {
1316 for (auto *output : pi.outputs()) {
1317 if (output->kind() == IOKind::Buffer) {
1318 internal_assert(!output->funcs().empty());
1319 for (const auto &f : output->funcs()) {
1320 user_assert(f.defined()) << "Output " << output->name() << " is not fully defined.";
1321 auto output_buffers = f.output_buffers();
1322 for (auto &o : output_buffers) {
1323 Parameter p = o.parameter();
1324 // This must use p.name(), *not* output->name()
1325 get_value_tracker()->track_values(p.name(), parameter_constraints(p));
1326 }
1327 }
1328 }
1329 }
1330 }
1331}

1333void GeneratorBase::check_min_phase(Phase expected_phase) const {
1334 user_assert(phase >= expected_phase) << "You may not do this operation at this phase.";
1335}
1336
1337void GeneratorBase::check_exact_phase(Phase expected_phase) const {
1338 user_assert(phase == expected_phase) << "You may not do this operation at this phase.";
1339}
1340
1341void GeneratorBase::advance_phase(Phase new_phase) {
1342 switch (new_phase) {
1343 case Created:
1344 internal_error << "Impossible";
1345 break;
1346 case ConfigureCalled:
1347 internal_assert(phase == Created);
1348 break;
1349 case InputsSet:
1350 internal_assert(phase == Created || phase == ConfigureCalled);
1351 break;
1352 case GenerateCalled:
1353 // It's OK to advance directly to GenerateCalled.
1354 internal_assert(phase == Created || phase == ConfigureCalled || phase == InputsSet);
1355 break;
1356 case ScheduleCalled:
1357 internal_assert(phase == GenerateCalled);
1358 break;
1359 }
1360 phase = new_phase;
1361}
1362
1363void GeneratorBase::ensure_configure_has_been_called() {
1364 if (phase < ConfigureCalled) {
1365 call_configure();
1366 }
1367 check_min_phase(ConfigureCalled);
1368}

1377void GeneratorBase::pre_generate() {
1378 advance_phase(GenerateCalled);
1379 GeneratorParamInfo &pi = param_info();
1380 user_assert(!pi.outputs().empty()) << "Must use Output<> with generate() method.";
1381 user_assert(get_target() != Target()) << "The Generator target has not been set.";
1382
1383 if (!inputs_set) {
1384 for (auto *input : pi.inputs()) {
1385 input->init_internals();
1386 }
1387 inputs_set = true;
1388 }
1389 for (auto *output : pi.outputs()) {
1390 output->init_internals();
1391 }
1392 track_parameter_values(false);

1419 track_parameter_values(false);

1425
1426Pipeline GeneratorBase::get_pipeline() {
1427 check_min_phase(GenerateCalled);
1428 if (!pipeline.defined()) {
1429 GeneratorParamInfo &pi = param_info();
1430 user_assert(!pi.outputs().empty()) << "Must use get_pipeline<> with Output<>.";
1431 std::vector<Func> funcs;
1432 for (auto *output : pi.outputs()) {
1433 for (const auto &f : output->funcs()) {
1434 user_assert(f.defined()) << "Output \"" << f.name() << "\" was not defined.\n";
1435 if (output->dims_defined()) {
1436 user_assert(f.dimensions() == output->dims()) << "Output \"" << f.name()
1437 << "\" requires dimensions=" << output->dims()
1438 << " but was defined as dimensions=" << f.dimensions() << ".\n";
1439 }
1440 if (output->types_defined()) {
1441 user_assert((int)f.outputs() == (int)output->types().size()) << "Output \"" << f.name()
1442 << "\" requires a Tuple of size " << output->types().size()
1443 << " but was defined as Tuple of size " << f.outputs() << ".\n";
1444 for (size_t i = 0; i < f.output_types().size(); ++i) {
1445 Type expected = output->types().at(i);
1446 Type actual = f.output_types()[i];
1447 user_assert(expected == actual) << "Output \"" << f.name()
1448 << "\" requires type " << expected
1449 << " but was defined as type " << actual << ".\n";
1450 }
1451 }
1452 funcs.push_back(f);
1453 }
1454 }
1455 pipeline = Pipeline(funcs);
1456 }
1457 return pipeline;
1458}
1459
1460Module GeneratorBase::build_module(const std::string &function_name,
1461 const LinkageType linkage_type) {
1462 AutoSchedulerResults auto_schedule_results;
1463 ensure_configure_has_been_called();
1464 Pipeline pipeline = build_pipeline();
1465 if (get_auto_schedule()) {
1466 auto_schedule_results = pipeline.auto_schedule(get_target(), get_machine_params());
1467 }
1468
1469 const GeneratorParamInfo &pi = param_info();
1470 std::vector<Argument> filter_arguments;
1471 for (const auto *input : pi.inputs()) {
1472 for (const auto &p : input->parameters_) {
1473 filter_arguments.push_back(to_argument(p));
1474 }
1475 }
1476
1477 Module result = pipeline.compile_to_module(filter_arguments, function_name, get_target(), linkage_type);
1478 std::shared_ptr<ExternsMap> externs_map = get_externs_map();
1479 for (const auto &map_entry : *externs_map) {
1480 result.append(map_entry.second);
1481 }
1482
1483 for (const auto *output : pi.outputs()) {
1484 for (size_t i = 0; i < output->funcs().size(); ++i) {
1485 auto from = output->funcs()[i].name();
1486 auto to = output->array_name(i);
1487 size_t tuple_size = output->types_defined() ? output->types().size() : 1;
1488 for (size_t t = 0; t < tuple_size; ++t) {
1489 std::string suffix = (tuple_size > 1) ? ("." + std::to_string(t)) : "";
1490 result.remap_metadata_name(from + suffix, to + suffix);
1491 }
1492 }
1493 }
1494
1495 result.set_auto_scheduler_results(auto_schedule_results);
1496
1497 return result;
1498}
1499
1500Module GeneratorBase::build_gradient_module(const std::string &function_name) {
1501 constexpr int DBG = 1;
1502
1503 // I doubt these ever need customizing; if they do, we can make them arguments to this function.
1504 const std::string grad_input_pattern = "_grad_loss_for_$OUT$";
1505 const std::string grad_output_pattern = "_grad_loss_$OUT$_wrt_$IN$";
1506 const LinkageType linkage_type = LinkageType::ExternalPlusMetadata;
1507
1508 user_assert(!function_name.empty()) << "build_gradient_module(): function_name cannot be empty\n";
1509
1510 ensure_configure_has_been_called();
1511 Pipeline original_pipeline = build_pipeline();
1512 std::vector<Func> original_outputs = original_pipeline.outputs();
1513
1514 // Construct the adjoint pipeline, which has:
1515 // - All the same inputs as the original, in the same order
1516 // - Followed by one grad-input for each original output
1517 // - Followed by one output for each unique pairing of original-output + original-input.
1518
1519 const GeneratorParamInfo &pi = param_info();
1520
1521 // Even though propagate_adjoints() supports Funcs-of-Tuples just fine,
1522 // we aren't going to support them here (yet); AFAICT, neither PyTorch nor
1523 // TF support Tensors with Tuples-as-values, so we'd have to split the
1524 // tuples up into separate Halide inputs and outputs anyway; since Generator
1525 // doesn't support Tuple-valued Inputs at all, and Tuple-valued Outputs
1526 // are quite rare, we're going to just fail up front, with the assumption
1527 // that the coder will explicitly adapt their code as needed. (Note that
1528 // support for Tupled outputs could be added with some effort, so if this
1529 // is somehow deemed critical, go for it)
1530 for (const auto *input : pi.inputs()) {
1531 const size_t tuple_size = input->types_defined() ? input->types().size() : 1;
1532 // Note: this should never happen
1533 internal_assert(tuple_size == 1) << "Tuple Inputs are not yet supported by build_gradient_module()";
1534 }
1535 for (const auto *output : pi.outputs()) {
1536 const size_t tuple_size = output->types_defined() ? output->types().size() : 1;
1537 internal_assert(tuple_size == 1) << "Tuple Outputs are not yet supported by build_gradient_module";
1538 }
1539
1540 std::vector<Argument> gradient_inputs;
1541
1542 // First: the original inputs. Note that scalar inputs remain scalar,
1543 // rather being promoted into zero-dimensional buffers.
1544 for (const auto *input : pi.inputs()) {
1545 // There can be multiple Funcs/Parameters per input if the input is an Array
1546 internal_assert(input->parameters_.size() == input->funcs_.size());
1547 for (const auto &p : input->parameters_) {
1548 gradient_inputs.push_back(to_argument(p));
1549 debug(DBG) << " gradient copied input is: " << gradient_inputs.back().name << "\n";
1550 }
1551 }
1552
1553 // Next: add a grad-input for each *original* output; these will
1554 // be the same shape as the output (so we should copy estimates from
1555 // those outputs onto these estimates).
1556 // - If an output is an Array, we'll have a separate input for each array element.
1557
1558 std::vector<ImageParam> d_output_imageparams;
1559 for (const auto *output : pi.outputs()) {
1560 for (size_t i = 0; i < output->funcs().size(); ++i) {
1561 const Func &f = output->funcs()[i];
1562 const std::string output_name = output->array_name(i);
1563 // output_name is something like "funcname_i"
1564 const std::string grad_in_name = replace_all(grad_input_pattern, "$OUT$", output_name);
1565 // TODO(srj): does it make sense for gradient to be a non-float type?
1566 // For now, assume it's always float32 (unless the output is already some float).
1567 const Type grad_in_type = output->type().is_float() ? output->type() : Float(32);
1568 const int grad_in_dimensions = f.dimensions();
1569 const ArgumentEstimates grad_in_estimates = f.output_buffer().parameter().get_argument_estimates();
1570 internal_assert((int)grad_in_estimates.buffer_estimates.size() == grad_in_dimensions);
1571
1572 ImageParam d_im(grad_in_type, grad_in_dimensions, grad_in_name);
1573 for (int d = 0; d < grad_in_dimensions; d++) {
1574 d_im.parameter().set_min_constraint_estimate(d, grad_in_estimates.buffer_estimates[i].min);
1575 d_im.parameter().set_extent_constraint_estimate(d, grad_in_estimates.buffer_estimates[i].extent);
1576 }
1577 d_output_imageparams.push_back(d_im);
1578 gradient_inputs.push_back(to_argument(d_im.parameter()));
1579
1580 debug(DBG) << " gradient synthesized input is: " << gradient_inputs.back().name << "\n";
1581 }
1582 }
1583
1584 // Finally: define the output Func(s), one for each unique output/input pair.
1585 // Note that original_outputs.size() != pi.outputs().size() if any outputs are arrays.
1586 internal_assert(original_outputs.size() == d_output_imageparams.size());
1587 std::vector<Func> gradient_outputs;
1588 for (size_t i = 0; i < original_outputs.size(); ++i) {
1589 const Func &original_output = original_outputs.at(i);
1590 const ImageParam &d_output = d_output_imageparams.at(i);
1591 Region bounds;
1592 for (int i = 0; i < d_output.dimensions(); i++) {
1593 bounds.emplace_back(d_output.dim(i).min(), d_output.dim(i).extent());
1594 }
1595 Func adjoint_func = BoundaryConditions::constant_exterior(d_output, make_zero(d_output.type()));
1596 Derivative d = propagate_adjoints(original_output, adjoint_func, bounds);
1597
1598 const std::string &output_name = original_output.name();
1599 for (const auto *input : pi.inputs()) {
1600 for (size_t i = 0; i < input->funcs_.size(); ++i) {
1601 const std::string input_name = input->array_name(i);
1602 const auto &f = input->funcs_[i];
1603 const auto &p = input->parameters_[i];
1604
1605 Func d_f = d(f);
1606
1607 std::string grad_out_name = replace_all(replace_all(grad_output_pattern, "$OUT$", output_name), "$IN$", input_name);
1608 if (!d_f.defined()) {
1609 grad_out_name = "_dummy" + grad_out_name;
1610 }
1611
1612 Func d_out_wrt_in(grad_out_name);
1613 if (d_f.defined()) {
1614 d_out_wrt_in(Halide::_) = d_f(Halide::_);
1615 } else {
1616 debug(DBG) << " No Derivative found for output " << output_name << " wrt input " << input_name << "\n";
1617 // If there was no Derivative found, don't skip the output;
1618 // just replace with a dummy Func that is all zeros. This ensures
1619 // that the signature of the Pipeline we produce is always predictable.
1620 std::vector<Var> vars;
1621 for (int i = 0; i < d_output.dimensions(); i++) {
1622 vars.push_back(Var::implicit(i));
1623 }
1624 d_out_wrt_in(vars) = make_zero(d_output.type());
1625 }
1626
1627 d_out_wrt_in.set_estimates(p.get_argument_estimates().buffer_estimates);
1628
1629 // Useful for debugging; ordinarily better to leave out
1630 // debug(0) << "\n\n"
1631 // << "output:\n" << FuncWithDependencies(original_output) << "\n"
1632 // << "d_output:\n" << FuncWithDependencies(adjoint_func) << "\n"
1633 // << "input:\n" << FuncWithDependencies(f) << "\n"
1634 // << "d_out_wrt_in:\n" << FuncWithDependencies(d_out_wrt_in) << "\n";
1635
1636 gradient_outputs.push_back(d_out_wrt_in);
1637 debug(DBG) << " gradient output is: " << d_out_wrt_in.name() << "\n";
1638 }
1639 }
1640 }
1641
1642 Pipeline grad_pipeline = Pipeline(gradient_outputs);
1643
1644 AutoSchedulerResults auto_schedule_results;
1645 if (get_auto_schedule()) {
1646 auto_schedule_results = grad_pipeline.auto_schedule(get_target(), get_machine_params());
1647 } else {
1648 user_warning << "Autoscheduling is not enabled in build_gradient_module(), so the resulting "
1649 "gradient module will be unscheduled; this is very unlikely to be what you want.\n";
1650 }
1651
1652 Module result = grad_pipeline.compile_to_module(gradient_inputs, function_name, get_target(), linkage_type);
1653 user_assert(get_externs_map()->empty())
1654 << "Building a gradient-descent module for a Generator with ExternalCode is not supported.\n";
1655
1656 result.set_auto_scheduler_results(auto_schedule_results);
1657
1658 return result;
1659}

1661void GeneratorBase::emit_cpp_stub(const std::string &stub_file_path) {
1662 user_assert(!generator_registered_name.empty() && !generator_stub_name.empty()) << "Generator has no name.\n";
1663 // Make sure we call configure() so that extra inputs/outputs are added as necessary.
1664 ensure_configure_has_been_called();
1665 // StubEmitter will want to access the GP/SP values, so advance the phase to avoid assert-fails.

1671 emit.emit();
1672}

1795
1796void GIOBase::verify_internals() {
1797 user_assert(dims_ >= 0) << "Generator Input/Output Dimensions must have positive values";
1798
1799 if (kind() != IOKind::Scalar) {
1800 for (const Func &f : funcs()) {
1801 user_assert(f.defined()) << "Input/Output " << name() << " is not defined.\n";
1802 user_assert(f.dimensions() == dims())
1803 << "Expected dimensions " << dims()
1804 << " but got " << f.dimensions()
1805 << " for " << name() << "\n";
1806 user_assert(f.outputs() == 1)
1807 << "Expected outputs() == " << 1
1808 << " but got " << f.outputs()
1809 << " for " << name() << "\n";
1810 user_assert(f.output_types().size() == 1)
1811 << "Expected output_types().size() == " << 1
1812 << " but got " << f.outputs()
1813 << " for " << name() << "\n";
1814 user_assert(f.output_types()[0] == type())
1815 << "Expected type " << type()
1816 << " but got " << f.output_types()[0]
1817 << " for " << name() << "\n";
1818 }
1819 } else {
1820 for (const Expr &e : exprs()) {
1821 user_assert(e.defined()) << "Input/Ouput " << name() << " is not defined.\n";
1822 user_assert(e.type() == type())
1823 << "Expected type " << type()
1824 << " but got " << e.type()
1825 << " for " << name() << "\n";
1826 }
1827 }

1844 user_assert(types().at(i) == t.at(i)) << "Type mismatch for " << name() << ": expected " << types().at(i) << " saw " << t.at(i);

1912 GIOBase::verify_internals();
1913

1919void GeneratorInputBase::init_internals() {
1920 // Call these for the side-effect of asserting if the values aren't defined.
1921 (void)array_size();
1922 (void)types();
1923 (void)dims();
1924
1925 parameters_.clear();
1926 exprs_.clear();
1927 funcs_.clear();
1928 for (size_t i = 0; i < array_size(); ++i) {
1929 auto name = array_name(i);
1930 parameters_.emplace_back(type(), kind() != IOKind::Scalar, dims(), name);
1931 auto &p = parameters_[i];
1932 if (kind() != IOKind::Scalar) {
1933 internal_assert(dims() == p.dimensions());
1934 funcs_.push_back(make_param_func(p, name));
1935 } else {
1936 Expr e = Internal::Variable::make(type(), name, p);
1937 exprs_.push_back(e);
1938 }
1939 }
1940
1941 set_def_min_max();
1942 verify_internals();
1943}

1945void GeneratorInputBase::set_inputs(const std::vector<StubInput> &inputs) {
1946 generator->check_exact_phase(GeneratorBase::InputsSet);
1947 parameters_.clear();
1948 exprs_.clear();
1949 funcs_.clear();
1950 check_matching_array_size(inputs.size());
1951 for (size_t i = 0; i < inputs.size(); ++i) {
1952 const StubInput &in = inputs.at(i);
1953 user_assert(in.kind() == kind()) << "An input for " << name() << " is not of the expected kind.\n";
1954 if (kind() == IOKind::Function) {
1955 auto f = in.func();
1956 user_assert(f.defined()) << "The input for " << name() << " is an undefined Func. Please define it.\n";
1957 check_matching_types(f.output_types());
1958 check_matching_dims(f.dimensions());
1959 funcs_.push_back(f);
1960 parameters_.emplace_back(f.output_types().at(0), true, f.dimensions(), array_name(i));
1961 } else if (kind() == IOKind::Buffer) {
1962 auto p = in.parameter();
1963 user_assert(p.defined()) << "The input for " << name() << " is an undefined Buffer. Please define it.\n";
1964 check_matching_types({p.type()});
1965 check_matching_dims(p.dimensions());
1966 funcs_.push_back(make_param_func(p, name()));
1967 parameters_.push_back(p);
1968 } else {
1969 auto e = in.expr();
1970 user_assert(e.defined()) << "The input for " << name() << " is an undefined Expr. Please define it.\n";
1971 check_matching_types({e.type()});
1972 check_matching_dims(0);
1973 exprs_.push_back(e);
1974 parameters_.emplace_back(e.type(), false, 0, array_name(i));
1975 }
1976 }
1977
1978 set_def_min_max();
1979 verify_internals();
1980}

1982void GeneratorInputBase::set_estimate_impl(const Var &var, const Expr &min, const Expr &extent) {
1983 internal_assert(exprs_.empty() && !funcs_.empty() && parameters_.size() == funcs_.size());
1984 for (size_t i = 0; i < funcs_.size(); ++i) {
1985 Func &f = funcs_[i];
1986 f.set_estimate(var, min, extent);
1987 // Propagate the estimate into the Parameter as well, just in case
1988 // we end up compiling this for toplevel.
1989 std::vector<Var> args = f.args();
1990 int dim = -1;
1991 for (size_t a = 0; a < args.size(); ++a) {
1992 if (args[a].same_as(var)) {
1993 dim = a;
1994 break;
1995 }
1996 }
1997 internal_assert(dim >= 0);
1998 Parameter &p = parameters_[i];
1999 p.set_min_constraint_estimate(dim, min);
2000 p.set_extent_constraint_estimate(dim, extent);
2001 }
2002}
2003
2004void GeneratorInputBase::set_estimates_impl(const Region &estimates) {
2005 internal_assert(exprs_.empty() && !funcs_.empty() && parameters_.size() == funcs_.size());
2006 for (size_t i = 0; i < funcs_.size(); ++i) {
2007 Func &f = funcs_[i];
2008 f.set_estimates(estimates);
2009 // Propagate the estimate into the Parameter as well, just in case
2010 // we end up compiling this for toplevel.
2011 for (size_t dim = 0; dim < estimates.size(); ++dim) {
2012 Parameter &p = parameters_[i];
2013 const Range &r = estimates[dim];
2014 p.set_min_constraint_estimate(dim, r.min);
2015 p.set_extent_constraint_estimate(dim, r.extent);
2016 }
2017 }
